This package uses OASIS to generate its build system. See section OASIS for full
information.

Dependencies
============

In order to compile this package, you will need:
* ocaml (>= 3.12)
* findlib
* pkg-config
* efl (>= 1.11) and elementary (>= 1.11)
    from the Enlightenment Foundation Libraries (EFL)

In particular, to install elementary, you will need to install the other
libraries of the EFL.

Installing
==========

1. Uncompress source directory and go to the root of the package.
2. Run 'ocaml setup.ml -configure'
3. Run 'ocaml setup.ml -build'
5. (Optional) Run 'ocaml setup.ml -doc' to build the documentation
4. Run (as root if necessary) 'ocaml setup.ml -install'

To see available options for the configuration part, run
'ocaml setup.ml -configure -help'

Uninstalling
============

1. Go to the root of the package.
2. Run 'ocaml setup.ml -uninstall'

OASIS
=====

OASIS is a software that helps to write setup.ml using a simple '_oasis'
configuration file. The generated setup only depends on standard OCaml
installation, no additional library is required.

Homepage: http://oasis.forge.ocamlcore.org/

To see the different commands for setup.ml, run 'ocaml setup.ml -help'.

